        <h1 id="hledger"><a href="#hledger">hledger</a></h1>
<p>hledger is a computer program for easily tracking money, time, or other commodities, inspired by <a href="http://ledger-cli.org">ledger</a>. It is quite limited in features, but lightweight and reliable. For some, it is a bare-bones, simpler, less expensive alternative to Quicken or GnuCash. It is available for free under the GNU General Public License.</p>
<p>hledger aims to help both computer experts and regular folks gain clarity in their finances and time management, but currently it is a little more suited to techies. I use it every day to:</p>
<ul>
<li>track spending and income</li>
<li>see time reports by day/week/month/project</li>
<li>get accurate numbers for client billing and tax filing</li>
<li>track invoices</li>
</ul>
<p>hledger is first a command-line tool, but also provides a web interface (try the <a href="http://demo.hledger.org">demo</a>). Read the <a href="MANUAL.html">manual</a> to learn more, including <a href="FAQ.html#how-does-hledger-relate-to-ledger">how we are different from ledger</a>, and get started tracking your numbers!</p>
